---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Manage SIP Trunks - Provider Connectivity - GonoPBX" description="GonoPBX SIP trunks: connect providers via registration or IP authentication. Easy setup for Plusnet, Sipgate, Telekom, and more." lang="en">

  
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/en/sip-trunks" class="nav-logo">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="GonoPBX Logo" />
      </a>
      <button class="nav-toggle" id="navToggle" aria-label="Menu">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M3 12h18M3 6h18M3 18h18" />
        </svg>
      </button>
      <ul class="nav-links" id="navLinks">
        <li><a href="/en/#features">Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/#screenshots">Screenshots</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/#techstack">Technology</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/release-notes">Release Notes</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/blog/">Blog</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/kontakt">Contact</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/unterstuetzen">Support</a></li>
        <li class="nav-lang">
          <a href="/sip-trunks" class="lang-link">DE</a>
          <span class="lang-sep">|</span>
          <a href="/en/sip-trunks" class="lang-link active">EN</a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/ankaios76/gonopbx" class="nav-cta">GitHub</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </nav>


  <section class="blog-article">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/en/#features" class="blog-back-link">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="M12 19l-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
        Back to overview
      </a>

      <div class="blog-article-header">
        <div class="blog-card-meta" style="justify-content:center;">
          <span class="blog-card-tag">Feature</span>
          <span>Core capability</span>
        </div>
        <h1>SIP Trunks – Provider Connectivity Made Easy</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="blog-article-content">
        <p>
          SIP trunks connect your PBX to the public telephone network.
          GonoPBX supports <strong>registration and IP-based authentication</strong>
          and makes setup as easy as possible.
        </p>

        <h2>Features</h2>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Registration</strong> – Classic SIP registration with username and password</li>
          <li><strong>IP authentication</strong> – For providers that authenticate by IP address</li>
          <li><strong>Registration status</strong> – Live status whether the trunk is registered</li>
          <li><strong>Multiple trunks</strong> – Any number of provider connections at once</li>
          <li><strong>Codec configuration</strong> – Set codecs per trunk</li>
          <li><strong>NAT support</strong> – Automatic detection of external IP address</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Screenshot</h2>

        <div style="margin:32px 0;">
          <img src="/feature-sip-trunks.png" alt="SIP trunk management in GonoPBX" style="width:100%;border-radius:12px;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);" />
          <p style="text-align:center;color:#718096;font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px;">SIP trunk overview with registration status and configuration</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Supported providers</h2>

        <p>GonoPBX works with any standards-compliant SIP provider. Tested with:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Plusnet (IPfonie)</strong> – Registration with SIP credentials</li>
          <li><strong>Sipgate</strong> – SIP trunk with registration</li>
          <li><strong>Deutsche Telekom</strong> – All-IP / SIP trunk</li>
          <li><strong>easybell</strong> – SIP trunk with registration</li>
          <li>Any other RFC-3261 compliant SIP provider</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Setup</h2>

        <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:24px 0;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom:2px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:left;">
              <th style="padding:12px 16px;color:#4a5568;">Step</th>
              <th style="padding:12px 16px;color:#4a5568;">Action</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">1</td>
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">Settings → Lines → “New trunk”</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">2</td>
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">Choose provider type (registration or IP auth)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">3</td>
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">Enter SIP server, username, and password</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">4</td>
              <td style="padding:12px 16px;">Save – check registration status</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="blog-info-box">
          <p>
            <strong>Available since the first release.</strong>
            Trunk management is a core feature and continues to evolve with every release.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container">
      <ul class="footer-links">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/ankaios76/gonopbx">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://demo.gonopbx.de">Live Demo</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/unterstuetzen">Support</a></li>
        <li><a href="/impressum">Imprint</a></li>
        <li><a href="/datenschutz">Privacy</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>&copy; 2026 Norbert Hengsteler. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>


  <script>
    document.getElementById('navToggle')?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      document.getElementById('navLinks')?.classList.toggle('open');
    });
    document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a').forEach(link => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        document.getElementById('navLinks')?.classList.remove('open');
      });
    });
  </script>

</Layout>
